Response Text: I'd like to see more money go to individual artists and organizations in the music and film industries that keep people spending money in Austin the most. A *majority* of our HOT taxes go to a convention center that serves only 300,000 visitors per year. Filmmakers and musicians bring in MILLIONS of tourists and generate MILLIONS of jobs. Also, most of those ACC visitors are there for SXSW. The imbalance is staggering. Filmmakers and musicians deserve so much more and, in return, we have a real opportunity to make Austin a top destination for artists. But to keep growing with our city, we have to redistribute financial support from failed corporate interests like the ACC to the artists, festivals, and museums who keep Austin weird, creative, and thriving! (I realize this speech is really meant for elected officials who control the power of the municipal purse, but since the survey asked...Love ACME. Just hope you all get ALL the funds!)

